The Shoreline Monitor

The coast in this area is characterized by a diverse range of coastal change rates. The majority of the coastline exhibits stable conditions, with change rates between -0.5 and 0.5 m/yr. However, there are significant sections experiencing extreme accretion, particularly with rates exceeding 5 m/yr, and some areas showing intense erosion, with rates between -1 and -3 m/yr. Notably, isolated points display severe erosion, with rates below -5 m/yr, and extreme accretion, with rates surpassing 100 m/yr. This variability highlights the dynamic nature of the coastal processes in this region.
